(firstQuint)Instillation of Botox in the Bladder.

 Pilot study to evaluate the effect of instillation treatment with onabotulinumtoxin A (BOTOX(R)) in the urinary bladder using Electromotive Drug Application (EMDA) in women with overactive bladder.

 15 women with therapy-resistant OAB will be included.

 All patients must be qualified for conventional cystoscopic Botox injection.

 The study is not randomized or blinded.

 Follow-up time is six months with voiding charts and three questionnaires.

(UDI-6, IIQ-7, ICIQ-UI SF) as well as a satisfaction with treatment VAS.

